The paper discusses the computational challenges involved in reconstructing 3-D molecular structures using cryo-electron microscopy, which involves signal processing, estimation and detection theory, high-dimensional statistics, convex and non-convex optimization, spectral algorithms, dimensionality reduction, and machine learning. These topics are closely related to computer vision (cs.CV), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
